{"/service/ndnp/in/batch_in_ilia_ver01/data/sn87055779/00271740451/1930010201/0546.xml":{"full_text":"NEW\nYEAR'S\nr\nAND BEST WISHES\n1929 has been a wonderful year for Oliver\u2014 wonderful in business\nreturns\u2014wonderful in accomplishment\u2014wonderful in material foun\ndations laid for greater business in 1930 wonderful in happiness\nto all the thousands of loyal Oliver Wsrkers who have, by unselfish\nwork and co-operation, placed the names of South Bend and Oliver\nto the front in every state in the Union in every land where agri\nculture is practiced.\n1929 has seen Oliver, always a leader in the manufacture and sale\nof farm implements, enter the \"Big League\" of business as a division\nof the Oliver Farm Equipment Company, one of the leaders in the\ngreat farm equipment industry, with factories in South Bend, Charles\nCity, Battle Creek, Springfield, and La Crosse. It has seen our splendid\nfactory in South Bend improved, and production increased. It has\nseen loyal Oliver Workers promoted to greater responsibilities. It\nhas seen the foundations laid in South Bend for even greater indus\ntrial and business expansion. Yes I 1929 has been a great year for\nus here at Oliver.\nFor ail this growth and development, for the bright business outlook\nbefore us and for the unselfish co-operation and support of the\nthousands of sincere, forward looking home folks of South Bench\nOliver is thankful. It has been a great year in the inspiration and\nhelp that comes from understanding and friendship. It is our earnest\nwish that during the years ahead, this understanding may continue,\nthese friendships may grow, and that Oliver may continue to bring to\nSouth Bend\u2014the home of Oliver prosperity and happiness to eH,\nAll Oliver W>rkers agree that it is great to live among friends in a\nhome town like South Bend. And all Oliver Workers unite with the\nparent company in wishing all home folks in South Bend and vicinity,\na new year that will be happy in those material comforts, which\nalways Row from service unselfishly rendered.\nDivision or\nOliver Farm Equipment Company\nSouth Bend, Indiana","height":"31744","width":"24040"}}
